<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-146-710  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 146 710.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>IEEE Transactions on Computers  April 1989 v38 n4 p493(8).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Diagnosis and repair of memory with coupling faults. (technical)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Chang, Ming-Feng; Fuchs, W. Kent; Patel, Janak H.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The problem of diagnosis and spare allocation for RAM withcoupling faults is examined, with a focus on utilizing spare rowsand columns.andP;  It is demonstrated that a coupling fault can berepaired by replacing a coupling cell with a spare row or acoupled cell with a spare row or column.andP;  Specifying both thecoupling cell and the coupled cell reduces the amount ofredundancy required for the repair of a given set of faults.andP;  Adiagnosis procedure for locating RAM stuck-at faults as well ascoupling faults is presented.andP;  The repair of coupled faults isdescribed using a graph model and a procedure to allocate rows andcolumns for repair is implemented.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     DiagnosticsRepairMemoryCouplingRAMFault ToleranceAlgorithms.andO;Feature:   illustrationchart.andO;Caption:   Two examples of coupling faults. (chart)Repair model stack for stuck-at faults and active coupling faults.andO;(chart)Flow chart of integrated diagnosis and repair. (chart)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>